result.execSummary:
The defendant Holden S. Monte was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Holden S. Monte is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Holden S. Monte was found guilty of Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Defendant Holden S. Monte in court with attorney Jonathan D. Sherman.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.  Atty Sherman agrees.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

Atty Sherman makes sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Ct 1:  Pay fine and costs = $442.00
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing in September
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Defendant Holden S. Monte in court with attorney Jonathan D. Sherman.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Sherman states that the defendant was having car troubles and asks that this be recalled as he is on his way.

BY THE COURT: Court will continue to 2:30pm.

BACK ON THE RECORD:
Defendant now appears in court.  
  Atty Hendee states that bond needs to be set along with booking.
 Atty Sherman states that the Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.    Defendant stands mute.  Attorney request the Court enter a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.

  Atty Hendee has no objection to a signature bond with conditions.
